===Etymology 1===
From French ''[[apostrophe#French|apostrophe]]'', or Latin ''[[apostrophus]]'', from Greek [[αποστροφος]] ‘accent of elision’, a noun use of an adjective from [[αποστρεφειν]] ‘turn away’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|orthography}} The text character '''’''', which is used to mark the [[possessive case]] ('s) or to show the [[omission]] of letters or numbers (''tho' '', ''they'll'', '' '65'').

